## Code conventions

- Kotlin standard formatting enforced by ktlint (`./gradlew ktlintFormat`)
- Prefer `val` over `var`; use immutable collections by default
- Use `data class` for value objects (entities, DTOs, responses)
- Use `sealed class` / `sealed interface` to model exhaustive domain states
- Use coroutines and `suspend` functions for all I/O; avoid blocking calls on the main dispatcher
- Null safety: use `?` types and safe-call operators (`?.`, `?:`); avoid `!!`
- Extension functions over utility classes
- No `System.exit()` or `Thread.sleep()` in library code — use structured concurrency
- Every public class and function has a KDoc comment
